<subSubSection pageId="26" pageNumber="291" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="26.[160,1156,1238,1333]" box="[160,252,1238,1264]" pageId="26" pageNumber="291">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,252,1238,1264]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="291">Ecology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[160,1156,1238,1333]" pageId="26" pageNumber="291">This is a pelagic species living in offshore waters and its life cycle has not been well studied.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="26" pageNumber="291" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="26.[160,1156,1384,1548]" box="[160,300,1384,1410]" pageId="26" pageNumber="291">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,300,1384,1410]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="291">Distribution</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[160,1156,1384,1548]" pageId="26" pageNumber="291">
Cosmopolitan; widely recorded in the Atlantic Ocean (
<bibRefCitation author="OBIS" box="[812,936,1419,1444]" pageId="26" pageNumber="291" pagination="22" refId="ref21226" refString="OBIS. 2021. Ocean Biogeographic Information System. Intergovernmental Oceanographic Commission of UNESCO. Accessed 2021 May 22. www. iobis. org" type="journal article" year="2021">OBIS 2021</bibRefCitation>
). 
<collectingCountry box="[962,1062,1419,1444]" name="Portugal" pageId="26" pageNumber="291">Portugal</collectingCountry>
, Canary Islands, Strait of 
<collectingCountry box="[372,472,1454,1479]" name="Gibraltar" pageId="26" pageNumber="291">Gibraltar</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Cervera JL &amp; Calado G &amp; Gavaia C &amp; Malaquias MAE &amp; Templado J &amp; Ballesteros M &amp; Megina C &amp; Garcia-Gomez JC" box="[492,730,1454,1479]" pageId="26" pageNumber="291" pagination="5 - 111" refId="ref18631" refString="Cervera JL, Calado G, Gavaia C, Malaquias MAE, Templado J, Ballesteros M, Megina C, Garcia-Gomez JC. 2004. An annotated and updated checklist of the opisthobranchs (Mollusca: Gastropoda) from Spain and Portugal (including Islands and archipelagos). Boletin-Instituto Espanol de Oceanografia. 20: 5 - 111." type="journal article" year="2004">Cervera et al. 2004</bibRefCitation>
); the Mediterranean Sea from the Andalusian coast (
<bibRefCitation author="Cervera JL &amp; Calado G &amp; Gavaia C &amp; Malaquias MAE &amp; Templado J &amp; Ballesteros M &amp; Megina C &amp; Garcia-Gomez JC" box="[373,598,1489,1514]" pageId="26" pageNumber="291" pagination="5 - 111" refId="ref18631" refString="Cervera JL, Calado G, Gavaia C, Malaquias MAE, Templado J, Ballesteros M, Megina C, Garcia-Gomez JC. 2004. An annotated and updated checklist of the opisthobranchs (Mollusca: Gastropoda) from Spain and Portugal (including Islands and archipelagos). Boletin-Instituto Espanol de Oceanografia. 20: 5 - 111." type="journal article" year="2004">Cervera et al. 2004</bibRefCitation>
), 
<collectingCountry box="[623,670,1489,1514]" name="Italy" pageId="26" pageNumber="291">Italy</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="OBIS" box="[687,809,1489,1514]" pageId="26" pageNumber="291" pagination="22" refId="ref21226" refString="OBIS. 2021. Ocean Biogeographic Information System. Intergovernmental Oceanographic Commission of UNESCO. Accessed 2021 May 22. www. iobis. org" type="journal article" year="2021">OBIS 2021</bibRefCitation>
), 
<collectingCountry box="[833,911,1489,1514]" name="Greece" pageId="26" pageNumber="291">Greece</collectingCountry>
(GBIF.org 2021) and Catalonia (this study).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="27" lastPageNumber="292" pageId="26" pageNumber="291" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="26.[160,1155,1598,1728]" box="[160,262,1598,1624]" pageId="26" pageNumber="291">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,262,1598,1624]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="291">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[160,1155,1598,1728]" pageId="26" pageNumber="291">Easily identified by its morphology, but since it is a cosmopolitan and scarcely studied species, of which often only the shell is found, several specimens were collected for sequencing.</paragraph>
